    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the skin from your <strong>smoked mackerel fillet[s]</strong> and discard</p><p>Chop the <strong>mackerel</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped mackerel</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until all the mackerel is coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated mackerel</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>coated mackerel</strong> and cook for 5-6 min, turning occasionally until golden and crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy mackerel</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>crispy mackerel</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Bash your <strong>cucumber[s]</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it into large, bite-sized pieces \u2013 this is your <strong>smashed cucumber</strong></p><p>Tip: Bash the cucumber in its bag to avoid mess. By bruising the cucumber, the water is drawn out more easily!</p><p>Add the <strong>smashed cucumber</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>quick-pickled smashed cucumber</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>mooli slaw</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>mayo </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>mooli slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Carefully wipe the reserved pan with some kitchen paper (it will be hot!) and return it to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the pan</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Give your eggs a little shake before you crack for perfectly centred yolks!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>gochujang </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>mirin</strong> to a bowl with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave </strong>for 30 secs or until the butter has melted \u2013 this is your <strong>bibimbap sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoked-mackerel-bibimbap-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cooked rice</strong> in a bowl and top with the <strong>crispy mackerel</strong>, <strong>quick-pickled smashed cucumber</strong> and <strong>mooli slaw</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>bibimbap sauce</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Tip: To eat this the Korean way, give everything a mix up to coat it all in the bibimbap sauce</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
